The paper focuses on game-theoretic approaches to network centrality, which suggests that it would likely fall under the category of cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). Additionally, the paper discusses algorithms and complexity, which could place it in the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the properties of coalitions and the value of groups of nodes, which could place it in the categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks).
